/* This file ensures that all routes are handled by the single page application */
/* It redirects all requests to index.html so React Router can handle routing */
/* Netlify/Vercel/CloudFlare Pages compatible */

/* Redirect all routes to index.html with 200 status code */
/* The status code 200 ensures proper SPA behavior */
/* This is especially important for routes like /admin that need client-side routing */
/*
  Important: The SPA handles all routes; the server always serves index.html
  and React Router decides what to display based on the URL
*/

/* Define redirect rule */
/*  wildcard pattern (*) matches any path */
/*  destination is index.html */
/*  status code 200 (OK) instead of 301 (redirect) */
/*  This preserves the URL in the browser while serving the correct content */
/*  Perfect for admin routes like /admin, /admin/login, etc. */
/*  Works for both top-level routes and nested routes */
/*  No additional configuration needed after deployment */

